{:tx/id #hlc "1773937520/0/af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/agent "af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-8: Replace apply_budget_gate() with project_output() — the ACP pipeline gate (INV-BUDGET-007, INV-BUDGET-009). BACKGROUND: The current apply_budget_gate() in mod.rs does: (1) compute ceiling from command profile, (2) call enforce_ceiling() to byte-truncate human and agent text. This violates INV-BUDGET-006 (density monotonicity) and causes the truncation problem. The replacement project_output() does: (1) compute k_eff from BudgetCtx, (2) select ActivationStrategy via strategy_for_k_eff(), (3) if the command returned an ActionProjection, call projection.project(strategy.max_context_tokens()), (4) if the command returned legacy CommandOutput, fall back to enforce_ceiling() for backward compat. This is the CRITICAL integration point — it connects the ACP types to the main CLI pipeline. Commands migrate to ACP one at a time; legacy commands continue to use the old path. APPROACH: (1) Add project_output(output: CommandOutput, projection: Option<ActionProjection>, k_eff: f64) -> CommandOutput to mod.rs. (2) When projection is Some, render it at the appropriate strategy level and replace agent/human fields. (3) When None, fall back to apply_budget_gate(). (4) Wire into main.rs dispatch. Tests: (A) projection-mode output never contains [truncated]. (B) legacy-mode output still works. (C) project_output at k_eff=0.1 produces <= 20 tokens. (D) project_output at k_eff=1.0 includes full context. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs + crates/braid/src/main.rs"
